Steps for installing and configuring GIT in linux:

1) Download from here : https://git-scm.com/ (Follow the steps)
2) check if it is installed successfully : git --version
3) Create an account on github
4) Configure it with linux:
       git config --global user.name "github username"
       git config --global user.email "github email"
5) To check the git configurations :
       git config --list
    These informations are stored in home directory. "home/username/.gitconfig" 


